Class CSVIndexReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.java.invertedIndex.CSVIndexReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IndexReader

    public class CSVIndexReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements IndexReader
    This implementation of IndexReader reads an Index object from the disk, with a format similar to CSV.
    Example: term, documentId:DocumentFrequency,documentId:DocumentFrequency, ...
    Since:
    10-16-2017
    See Also:
    CSV

      • parseToIndex

        public Index parseToIndex(java.io.File indexFile)
        This function parses the file that contains the invertedIndex, reads the header from file which indicates the type of Tokenizer used in the indexation, after that loads an Index object with terms and their respective Posting lists.
        Specified by:
